Description: Large section (two fragments joined) of the body and neck of a pale-red pottery wine-jar with convex body and cylindrical neck, the fabric is light-brown in section and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
